    <h2>Concepts</h2>
    <p>participatory ergonomics</p>
    <p>boundary objects</p>
    <p></p>
    <h2>Quotations</h2>
    <p>"Based on two case studies, we identify eight characteristics of boundary
      objects and their use, which make them particularly useful in PE design
      processes...The framework developed may serve to provide criteria to guide
      practitioners and intervention researchers in the selection of objects to
      facilitate a PE process."</p>
    <p>"Prototypes are physical or digital representations of a future artifact.
      Prototyping refers to the mutual learning process that takes place in a
      collaborative design setting."</p>
    <p></p>
    <h2>References</h2>
    <p>Carlile (2002)and Wenger (2000) - for categorising boundary objects</p>
    <p>Brodersen et al (2008) - collaborative prototyping as mutual learning
      process</p>
